         <abstract>
            <p>A comparison of the S&amp;P 500's implied annual return with a required equity return yields an estimate of the risk-adjusted excess return for the S&amp;P 500. This market excess return provides a measure of the attractiveness of stocks relative to the risk-free rate. Specific levels of excess return may be used to allocate cash flow between equities and cash, or between equities and stock index futures.</p>
